OL,3,CNew antiobiotic for UTIs approved for
OL,4,Cfirst time in three decades
OL,6,FA new antibiotic for treating urinary
OL,7,Ftract infections (UTIs) has been given
OL,8,Fthe green light by UK regulators, for
OL,9,Fthe first time in almost three decades.
OL,11,FGepotidacin, also known as Blujepa,
OL,12,Fcan be used by women in the UK who
OL,13,Fsuffer recurring infections, the
OL,14,FMedicines and Healthcare products
OL,15,FRegulatory Agency (MHRA) said.
OL,17,FThe drug's active ingredient also
OL,18,Fmakes it more difficult for bacteria
OL,19,Fto become resistant to treatment,
OL,20,Fwhich is crucial in tackling
OL,21,Fantibiotic resistance.
